(-1,\infty)
x' = \frac{-x}{1 + t}
x(t_{0}) = x_{0}
x(t) = x(t_{0})\frac{1 + t_{0}}{1 + t}
x(t)
\int 1/x \,dx = \int -1/(1+t)\,dt
\ln|x|=-\ln|1+t|+C
|x| = e^{-\ln|1+t|+C}
|x|=e^{\ln|(1+t)^{-1}|}e^C
x
x=Ce^{\ln|(1+t)^{-1}|}=C(1+t)^{-1}
x_0 = x(t_0)=C(1+t_0)^{-1}
C=x_0(1+t_0)
